The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bedi, Viswanath for ZCA city camp

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Former India captains Bishan Singh Bedi and Gundappa Viswanath will be in the city next week to train the boys at the Zonal Cricket Academy camp. 

Bedi and Viswanath, who will start work on Monday, are expected to spend five days with the trainees during their stay. 

The camp started on Saturday under the guidance of chief coach Bharat Arun. 

All the campers batting and bowling actions are being video-recorded and would be analysed by Bedi and Viswanath. 

Among the 22 players in the camp, four are from Bengal, namely ? Sreevats Goswami, Amit Banerjee, Rohan Banerjee and Amit Das. 

Five players are from Assam ? Pervez Aziz, Shib Shankar Roy, Abu Nachim Ahmed, Krishna Das and Sujoy Tarafdar. 

Six from Orissa, five from Jharkhand and two players from Tripura complete the list. 




